#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
archguard – professional security hardening & audit framework for Arch Linux
version 4.0.0

Modular, reversible hardening plus deep-scan audit suite.
Every change is backed up, checksummed, and logged to journald.
Every audit produces timestamped reports. Nothing is silent.

THREAT MODEL:
  Personal workstation or laptop requiring high assurance. Assumes the
  operator is technically competent and willing to review findings.
  NOT a CIS-benchmark tool. NOT a replacement for SELinux in a
  multi-tenant or server environment. Will NOT withstand nation-state
  adversaries. Will significantly raise the cost of opportunistic attacks.

DESIGN PRINCIPLES:
  1. No silent failures – every subprocess result is checked.
  2. Atomic writes only – no partial-file corruption.
  3. Every change is reversible unless explicitly marked otherwise.
  4. Pre-flight checks before any mutation.
  5. Read-only audit paths never touch the filesystem.
  6. Signal safety – Ctrl-C triggers rollback, not corruption.
  7. Structured findings – machine-readable JSON + human report.
  8. Idempotent – running twice is safe.

REQUIREMENTS:
  Python 3.10+  (uses match, Path.unlink(missing_ok=True), …)
  Arch Linux with pacman, systemctl, journalctl, sysctl, nft.
  Optional: rkhunter, lynis, aide, clamav, nmap, mokutil,
            apparmor, firejail, audit, apparmor-utils.

Usage:
  sudo archguard apply firewall --profile workstation --verify
  sudo archguard apply --preset hardened --force
       archguard audit --preset quick_audit
       archguard audit --preset full_audit --install-deps
       archguard status
       archguard report --verbose
       archguard revert firewall
       archguard backups --days 7
       archguard doctor
"""

